title: GRAMMYs 2017: Complete winners list
text:
Feb 12th 2017 4:55PM 
Music's biggest night is here! 
The 49th Annual GRAMMYs will honor the best in music on Sunday night. The star-studded ceremony will be broadcast live on CBS at 8 p.m. EST. SEE ALSO: GRAMMYs 2017 cheat sheet: Everything you need to know ahead of music's biggest night! 
The biggest question heading into the night is whether Beyoncé or Adele will reign supreme -- or if someone else will sneak in and snag the night's top awards. 
The massively popular singers are set to face off in the night's biggest categories, including Album of the Year. Adele's "25" and Beyoncé's "Lemonade" will take on fellow nominees -- Justin Bieber's "Purpose," Drake's "Views" and Sturgill Simpson's "A Sailors Guide To Earth -- in that category. 
Another big question mark heading into the night? Who will take home the coveted Best New Artist trophy? Most experts are predicting The Chainsmokers will run away with it, though Chance The Rapper is widely thought of as the deserving recipient. 
We'll have an updating list of the night's winners right here.
